DataElement.preferredName: Protocol Agent Transfer Administration Performed Study Activity Reason Code ISO21090.DSET.CD.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The completed action in which an authorized party at a designated study site dispenses or receives a study agent to/from a study subject. EXAMPLE(S): StudySubject receives a bottle of pills. A coded value specifying the motivation, cause, or rationale of an activity. EXAMPLE(S): routine requirement, drug reaction, infectious disease reporting requirement, on patient request
